    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ærzæ" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d3517e66" type="lemma"><orth>ærzæ</orth><form xml:id="form_d3517e68" type="variant"><orth>ærʒæ</orth></form></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3517e71"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>несметное число</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>infinite</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3517e83">
                        <quote>sædæ sædæ æmæ ærzæ sædæ<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (говорится
                                о необъятном множестве)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                (of vast number)</note></quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сто раз сто и %særzæ%s раз сто</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>take hundred hundred times and take hundred %særzæ%s times</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3517e103">
                        <quote>Nartæ æržæ æmæ sædæ wydysty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Нартов было тысяча и сто</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there were a thousand and hundred of the Narts</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I
                            29</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3517e122">
                        <quote>kæd raskʼærat sædæ sædæ sædsiwættæ, æržæ sædæ īwsiwættæ…</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>если вы пригоните сто раз сто сторогих (быков), тысячу раз сто
                                однорогих…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>if you bring hundred of hundred-horned bulls hundred times,
                                one-horned bulls thousand times…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I
                            50</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3517e141">
                        <quote>sædæ sædæ æmæ ærzæ sædæ nyččagta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он истребил сто раз сто и тысячу раз сто</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he destroyed a hundred times hundred and a thousand times hundred</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I
                            22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3517e160">
                        <quote>Æxsærtæggati æfsædtæ ærzæ æma ærzæ mini æncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>войска Ахсартаговых составляют тысячу и тысячу тысяч</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Æxsærtæggats’ army containes thousand people and thousand people
                                thousand times</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 45,
                                183%l124%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e182" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*hazahra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>тысяча</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e190" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>hazār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e195" xml:lang="x-nuristan"><lang/>
                        <w>azār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e200" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*zār(z’r)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e205" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>ysāra(-*zāra)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e211" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>*azar</w></mentioned><bibl/>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e217" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>haza%brə%bra-</w></mentioned>,<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e222" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>sahasra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>тысяча</q></gloss></mentioned>. Из персидского, частью, может
                    быть, из аланского (отсутствие начального %ih%i), слово усвоено в ряд кавказских
                    языков: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e230" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>azar</w></mentioned>,<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e235" xml:lang="lbe"><lang/>
                        <w>āzar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e241" xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>aǧzur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e246" xml:lang="tab"><lang/>
                        <w>ǧazur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e251" xml:lang="tab"><w>āzur</w></mentioned>;
                    ср. также <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e254" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>azari</w>
                        <gloss><q>сотня зверей, убитых охотником</q></gloss></mentioned> %b(пшав.)%b
                    azari („он сделал 3 азара“ = „убил 300 зверей“) (<bibl><author>Важа
                            Пшавела.</author><biblScope>Этногр. сочинения, 1937, стр.
                            153</biblScope></bibl> ). Звуковая история <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e266" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ærzæ</w></mentioned>. Ударение на первом слоге в *%iházahra%i- повлекло
                    редукцию, а затем исчезновение второго гласного; %ih%i исчезло, как обычно (ср.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncæ"/> (из %ihanti%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_max"/>]; образовавшаяся в результате группа -%izr%i-
                    неизбежно подверглась метатезе -%irz%i-. - Мы имеем, стало быть: *%iházahra%i →
                    *%iazara%i → *%iаz%rа%rrа%i → *%iazra%i → %iærzæ%i. Ср. вполне аналогичную
                    картину в развитии <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e276" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>kasyapa</w></mentioned>→ <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e281" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>xæfs(æ)</w>
                        <gloss><q>лягушка</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e289" xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>ezēr</w></mentioned> (~ %iezre%i) ‘тысяча’, если оно не унаследовано от
                    древнейших сношений угро-финнов с арийцами (см.: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Jacobsohn"/><biblScope>Arier u
                        Ugro-finnen</biblScope></bibl>), могло быть усвоено из аланского. В
                    последнем случае мы получаем terminus ante quem nоn для вышеописанных звуковых
                    изменений (*%iazara%i → %iærzæ%i): эти изменения должны были произойти после
                    осетино-венгерского соседства, т. е. после VII—VIII в. В то время как %iærzæ%i
                    удержалось только в эпосе в значении неопределенного множества, для ‘тысячи’
                    осетинский (вместе с кабардинским) усвоил <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e299" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>mīn</w></mentioned> q.
                            v.%n<bibl><author>Munkácsi,</author><biblScope>Magyar Nyelvor, 1933,
                            стр. 68, 89 сл</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>22, 168, 252
                    прим.</biblScope></bibl></etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e314" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*hazahra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>тысяча</q></gloss></mentioned>; compare <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e322" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>hazār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e327" xml:lang="x-nuristan"><lang/>
                        <w>azār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e332" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*zār(z’r)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e337" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>ysāra(-*zāra)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e343" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>*azar</w></mentioned><bibl/>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e349" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>haza%brə%bra-</w></mentioned>,<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e354" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>sahasra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>thousand</q></gloss></mentioned>. The word was brought in a number
                    of Caucaus languages through Persian and maybe partly from Alan (the lack of the
                    initial %ih%i): <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e362" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>azar</w></mentioned>,<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e367" xml:lang="lbe"><lang/>
                        <w>āzar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e373" xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>aǧzur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e378" xml:lang="tab"><lang/>
                        <w>ǧazur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e383" xml:lang="tab"><w>āzur</w></mentioned>;
                    see also <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e386" xml:lang="ka" dialect="ka-x-pshav"><lang/>
                        <w>azari</w>
                        <gloss><q>a hundred animals killed by the hunter</q></gloss></mentioned>
                    ("he made 3 azars“ = "he killed 300 animals") (<bibl><author>Важа
                            Пшавела.</author><biblScope>Этногр. сочинения, 1937, стр.
                            153</biblScope></bibl> ). The phonetic history of <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e398" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ærzæ</w></mentioned> is clear. The stress on the first syllable in
                    *%iházahra%i- entailed the reduction and then the loss of the second vowel;
                    %ih%i has been lost, like always [compare <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æncæ"/>
                    (from %ihanti%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_max"/>]; the group -%izr%i-
                    which has appeared as a result of these processes underwent metathesis -%irz%i-.
                    Hence, we have: *%iházahra%i → *%iazara%i → *%iаz%rа%rrа%i → *%iazra%i →
                    %iærzæ%i. Compare quite similar development in <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e408" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>kasyapa</w></mentioned>→ <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e413" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>xæfs(æ)</w>
                        <gloss><q>frog</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e421" xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>ezēr</w></mentioned> (~ %iezre%i) ‘thousand’, if it was not inherited
                    from ancient contacts of Finno-ugrians with the Indo-Iranians (see <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Jacobsohn"/><biblScope>Arier u
                            Ugro-finnen</biblScope></bibl>), could have been borrowed from Alan. In
                    the latter case we have %iterminus ante quem nоn%i for the sound changes
                    decribed above (*%iazara%i → %iærzæ%i): these changes had to happen after
                    Ossetic-Hungarian neighbourhood, this means after VII—VIII c. While %iærzæ%i is
                    now retained only in the epics in the meaning of indefinite multitude, Ossetic
                    (and Kabardian) has borrowed <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3517e431" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>mīn</w></mentioned> q. v. for
                            'thousand'%n<bibl><author>Munkácsi,</author><biblScope>Magyar Nyelvor,
                            1933, p. 68, 89 сл</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>22, 168, 252
                    прим.</biblScope></bibl></etym>
